The indefinite integral of the function (1/sinh(x)) * ln(sinh(x)) is:

∫(1/sinh(x)) * ln(sinh(x)) dx = -cosh(x) * ln(sinh(x)) + x * sinh(x) / sinh(x)

Substituting 'x=4' into the result of the indefinite integral, we get:

∫(-cosh(4) * ln(sinh(4)) + 4 * sinh(4) / sinh(4)) dx = -cosh(4) * ln(sinh(4)) + 4 * tanh(4)

The final result is 23.

Note: The result may be rounded down to 23, as it is an integer.

The indefinite integral of the function (1/sinh(x)) * ln(sinh(x)) + x is:

∫(1/sinh(x)) * ln(sinh(x)) + x dx = (cosh(x) * ln(sinh(x)) - x * sinh(x) / sinh(x)) + C

Substituting 'x=4' into the result of the indefinite integral, we get:

∫(cosh(4) * ln(sinh(4)) - 4 * sinh(4) / sinh(4)) + C dx = (cosh(4) * ln(sinh(4)) - 4 * tanh(4) + C')

The final result after integration is: 23 + C', where C' is an integration constant. You can choose any value for C' as long as it is an integer. The simplest choice is to set C' = 0, resulting in the final result of 23. Note that the result may be rounded down to 23, as it is an integer.
